HEADWORD: cedarwood
<hw>ce"dar*wood`</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The durable aromatic wood of
any of numerous cedar and cedarlike trees; especially the wood of the
red cedar, often used for cedar chests.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cedar.</syn>⟦br⟧
